{
  "stem": "7337.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was near the brewery, what was then the brewery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my dad said, let's go for a walk before dinner.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember very clearly we came out, and we saw a white man kick a newspaper vendor, black newspaper vendor, a boy, literally off the pavement with one kick.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And nobody even turned a head, and I thought to myself, what sort of a country have I arrived in?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, people don't even stop when they see that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was my first impression of what eventually became Apartheid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that existed in 1936.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody turned around.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we stayed [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in a place called the Rio Grande, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was opposite the brewery, just off Commissioner Street, for about six months.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we moved into Buckingham Court, which was opposite the Wellman Street shoe.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a brand new block of flats.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were the first tenants.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think we had a two-room-- a three-room flat for 16 guineas, which was the height of luxury as far as South Africa was then concerned.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I went to the technical college to take shorthand typing in order to learn English phonetically, because I was told that English is a language that is not pronounced the way it's written.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I learned it phonetically, because people said to me, you can always learn to write it later.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But first you must learn to speak it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took a course of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] English shorthand typing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the teacher told me, well, whilst you're about it, why don't you also take bookkeeping?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's the same course.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
